The paper deals with distributed network construction protocols, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The protocols involve pairwise interactions between processes, which suggests the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the expected time to convergence of the protocols, which involves analyzing the performance of the system, indicating the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper presents lower bounds for network construction problems, which suggests the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Turing Machines in network construction, which falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
